they doing anything but watching for a spawn?  I really don't<br>see how this could be construed as a camp.  There is no effort involved<br>other than monitoring for the appearance of a long term spawn.<br>You could do this quite easily with a twink ranger/druid on a second<br>account.  Having 5 or 6 people sitting there with you does not<br>make it any more official or noteworthy except that maybe you could<br>farm spells or experience while tracking/waiting for a rare spawn.<br>I just do not see the new skyfire Ragefire as being a campable mob.<br><br>The old ragefire was only marginally campable.  You did not have<br>to kill FG's to spawn him.  He would spawn with or without the FG's<br>being killed but Innoruuks old Nagy/Vox policy was followed in that<br>whoever got to the FG&quot;s or kept them cleared was considered <br>camping him and this was actually reasonable as there was effort<br>involved and it was a camp.  <br><br>Just my thoughts on the subject.  I still need Ragefire for my own<br>epic.  But I will be having my druid (portHo twink) on a second account<br>sitting in Skyfire monitoring for Rage while I go about my business with<br>my cleric.  Nor will I be staying awake 24/7.  My druid will be logged in<br>skyfire while I am playing and if Rage pops we mobilize. If he doesn't pop<br>I will log for the night as per normal and check again next time I am on.<br>This is in my opinion, the only reasonable, sane way of doing this.<br><br><br>Bohric<br>58th Cleric Inorruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ukaganfindel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaganfindel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/11/02 12:25:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1113.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web4.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/49/2436849.jpg?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is a Camp?</span><hr size=1> Camping is sitting in the same place, killing the same set of creatures over and over.  There isn't any more to it than that.<br><br>I don't know as there is any way a body *could* lay claim to the Ragefire spawn.  It really is just a matter of catching him when he's up.  I'll grant you, it's not easy to do as the Kunark dragons tend to have lifetimes measurable in minutes, but somebody ends up killing them every time, so it must be possible.<br><br>Sime mobs just aren't campable. <p><img src="http://web4.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/39/2383739.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uugle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ugle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ally Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/11/02 4:31:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1113.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://ugleduklin.tripod.com/sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/dscn0011s.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What is a Camp?</span><hr size=1> It's like running through S. Ro and having someone zone in and say they are camping the AC.  Sucks if you're running around clearing everything in the sand except the vendors and someone else get the spawn, but you agro it you got it.  I see a camp as a static area where a certain number of MOB's spawn and where your group OCCUPIES.  If you then want to pull from UZO or whatnot, go for it, but that's not part of &quot;your&quot; camp.  So the Guard spawn in Seb is a good example, or the Frenzy in Guk, or the Capt. in KC.  But to say you're camping Doom or claim Lodizal just doesn't fly.  <br><br>I used to see it in Guk quite a bit.  Sage group would claim the Ex, Sage, Cav, and Sav.  I quit doing camp checks, I'd just IU and head down.  If the Cav room didn't have anyone in it, I'd set up camp since it's an easy room to break and a good one to pull to.  The people pulling it would usually watch the pets eat the Wans, and leave us alone.  I have been in a Lord group pulling from the Lord to the Ex (including the Savant) because we could.  If someone else moved in and occupied one of the other &quot;camps&quot; then I'd make sure the rest of the group respected that.  CE is a camp, the Gargoyles that spawn just down from them I consider fair game.  Myconid king and his two lackeys is a camp, the Shrooms further out would be fair game.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ugregar1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gregar1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/11/02 4:55:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1113.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   What is a Camp?</span><hr size=1> a) The failure to program truly random loot on truly random spawns. b) The failure to program truly random spawn locations for specific MOB's with specific drops.<br>c) incredibly boring, but at the same time, apparently addictive.<br><br>Gregar Mataennoo<br>Ridgerunner<br>Ranger 53 <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showPrevMessage?topicID=1113.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showNextMessage?topicID=1113.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1113.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ichuu.com/AddReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.emailToFriend?topicID=1113.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.threadControl?topicID=1113.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1113.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.unsubscr